{"lemma":"أَمِيناتٌ","slug":"أَمِيناتٌ","root":"#.م.ن","root_slug":"_-م-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/_-م-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَمِين","root":"أمن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":14},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":14},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1268"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"reliable, trustworthy, loyal, responsible"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"upright, honest"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"faithful, true, truthful, authentic, honest, sincere, trusty, dependable"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"safe, secure","examples":[{"text":"وَهَٰذَا ٱلۡبَلَدِ ٱلۡأَمِينِ","english":"and this secure city ˹of Mecca˺!"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"innocuous, harmless"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"The archangel Gabriel","examples":[{"text":"نَزَلَ بِهِ ٱلرُّوحُ ٱلۡأَمِينُ","english":"which the trustworthy spirit ˹Gabriel˺ brought down"},{"text":"وَلَمَّا دَنَا الْمَوْتُ لِلْمُصْطَفَىٰ / وَعِنْدَ الرَّحِيلِ يَنَالُ الْمُنَىٰ / أَتَاهُ الْأَمِينُ بِمِسْكِ الْخِتَامْ / أَلَا فَلْتُبَلِّغْ جَمِيعَ الْأَنَامِ / حُشُودٌ تَرَاءَتْ بِأَرْضِ الْغَدِيرِ","english":"And when death drew closer to the Chosen one (Prophet Muhammad) / And during the departure he receives the will (of God) / The Trustworthy has come to him with the sweet conclusion / You shall report (it) to all creatures / Crowds witnessing in the land of Ghadeer"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"secretary"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"authorized representative, agent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"trustee, trusted person"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"chief, head, superintendent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"curator, custodian, sponsor, chamberlain"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"guarantor"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Ameen or Amin"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dual of أُمّ (ʔumm)","tags":["dual","form-of"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Related to أَمِنَ (ʔamina, “to be safe”), أَمُنَ (ʔamuna, “to be faithful”)."},"ipa":["/ʔa.miːn/","/ʔum.majn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1268","headword_ar":"اَمينٌ","root":"Amn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Trusted; trusted in; confided in;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, * S, * M, Msb, * K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~aAnN","text_ar":"اُمَّانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^omuwnN","text_ar":"مَاْمُونٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^otamanN","text_ar":"مُوْتَمَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (ISk, T, K:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person in whom one trusts"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confides; a confidant; a person intrusted with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to whom is confided, power, authority, control,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a charge,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY $aYo'K","text_ar":"عَلَى شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over a thing; a person intrusted with an affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with affairs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the management,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposal, thereof; a confidential agent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superintendent; a commissioner; a commissary; a trustee; a depositary;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a guardian:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trusty; trustworthy; trustful; confidential; faithful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb: *) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^umanaA='u","text_ar":"اُمَنَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and, accord. to some, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amanapN","text_ar":"اَمَنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in a trad. in which it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoHaAbiY A^amanapN liA^um~atiY","text_ar":"اَصْحَابِى اَمَنَةٌ لِاُمَّتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My companions are guardians to my people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to others, this is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=minN","text_ar":"ا=مِنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. in a sense mentioned below in this paragraph, so that the meaning in this trad. is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my companions are persons who accord trust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confidence, to my people"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) Hence,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^alamo taEolamiY yaA A^asoma wayoHaki A^an~aniY\n                      \n                     \n                        Halafotu yamiynFA laA A^axuwnu A^amiyniY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Knowest thou not, O Asmà"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asomaA='","text_ar":"اَسْمَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", curtailed for the sake of the metre),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mercy on thee!"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woe to thee! that I have sworn an oath that I will not act treacherously to him in whom I trust?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^omuwniY","text_ar":"مَاْمُونِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or the meaning here is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him who trusts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confides, in me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, T;) [i. e.] it is here"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=miniY","text_ar":"ا=مِنِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amiynu fiY AlqimaAri","text_ar":"الاَمِينُ فِى القِمَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujumidN","text_ar":"مُجُمِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amiynu","text_ar":"اَمِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqimaAri","text_ar":"القِمَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The person who is intrusted, as deputy, with the disposal of the arrows in the game called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almayosir","text_ar":"المَيْسِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he who shuffles the arrows;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~a*iY","text_ar":"الَّذِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaDoribu biAlqidaAHi","text_ar":"يَضْرِبُ بِالقِدَاحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (EM p. 105.) [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~uwHu AlA^amiynu","text_ar":"الرُّوحُ الاَمِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Trusted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Trusty, Spirit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Kur xxvi. 193;) applied to Gabriel, because he is intrusted with the revelation of God. (Bd.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~aAnN","text_ar":"اُمَّانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned above, and occurring in a verse of El-Aashà, applied to a merchant, is said by some to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Possessed of religion and excellence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^otamanN","text_ar":"مُوْتَمَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied, in a trad., to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^a*~in","text_ar":"مُوَذِّن"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning that men trust, or confide, in him with respect to the times in which he calls to prayer, and know by his call what they are commanded to do as to praying and fasting and breaking fast. (Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuEaAmalapi","text_ar":"المُعَامَلَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa maA^omuwnu","text_ar":"هُوَ مَاْمُونُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trusty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trustworthy, in dealing with others;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from exorbitance and deceit"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"artifice"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"craft to be feared."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An aid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assistant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawonN","text_ar":"عَوْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here app. meaning, as it often does,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an armed attendant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a guard"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because one trusts in his strength, and is without fear of his being weak. (M.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawiY~N","text_ar":"قَوِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA: [in the latter of which is given the same reason for this signification as is given in the M for that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewn","text_ar":"عون"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qwY","text_ar":"قوى"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be a mistranscription; but see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amuwnN","text_ar":"اَمُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b4-  One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who trusts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confides, in"},{"kind":"text","text":"another; (ISk, T, K;) [as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=minN","text_ar":"ا=مِنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha*irN","text_ar":"حَذِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] so accord. to ISk in the verse cited above in this paragraph: (T:) thus it bears two contr. significations. (K.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=minN","text_ar":"ا=مِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in five places.       -A2-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=miyna","text_ar":"ا=مِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"page_break","n":102}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","ISk","T","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}